<body>

<header>
  <h1>{{ lms_content_course_title }}</h1>
  <p>CyberRangeCZ &mdash; Hands-on Educational Platform &mdash; PUC2-Sub Case 2b</p>
</header>

<nav>
  <button class="active" onclick="showTab('overview', this)">Overview</button>
  <button onclick="showTab('module1', this)">Module 1 &mdash; Network Recon</button>
  <button onclick="showTab('module2', this)">Module 2 &mdash; Vuln Scanning</button>
  <button onclick="showTab('module3', this)">Module 3 &mdash; Reporting</button>
  <button onclick="showTab('exercise', this)">Practical Exercise</button>
</nav>

<main>

<!-- OVERVIEW TAB -->
<div id="overview" class="tab active">
  <div class="card">
    <span class="badge complete">Course Overview</span>
    <h2>Network Vulnerability Identification Training</h2>
    <p>This self-paced course trains you to identify network vulnerabilities using
       penetration testing techniques against a simulated CYNET-like lab environment.
       Complete all three theory modules before starting the practical exercise.</p>
    <h3>Learning Objectives</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Perform network reconnaissance to discover hosts, ports and services</li>
      <li>Conduct semi-automated vulnerability assessments using Nmap</li>
      <li>Map findings to known vulnerabilities (CVE/CVSS) and exploit vectors</li>
      <li>Compile a structured vulnerability report with prioritised remediation recommendations</li>
    </ol>
    <h3>Assessment Scoring</h3>
    <div class="score-grid">
      <div class="score-item"><div class="weight">35%</div><div class="label">Scan completeness (all key services identified)</div></div>
      <div class="score-item"><div class="weight">30%</div><div class="label">Vulnerability classification accuracy (CVE/CVSS)</div></div>
      <div class="score-item"><div class="weight">25%</div><div class="label">Remediation recommendation quality</div></div>
      <div class="score-item"><div class="weight">10%</div><div class="label">Report clarity and documentation standards</div></div>
    </div>
    <h3>Target Network</h3>
    <p>Your lab target network:</p>
    <div class="url-box">10.20.40.0/24 &mdash; target host: 10.20.40.10</div>
    <h3>Your Report Repository</h3>
    <p>Submit your vulnerability report to Gitea:</p>
    <div class="url-box">http://report-repo.internal:3000/</div>
    <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="showTab('module1', document.querySelectorAll('nav button')[1])">Start with Module 1 &rarr;</button>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- MODULE 1 TAB -->
<div id="module1" class="tab">
  <div class="card">
    <span class="badge theory">Theory</span>
    <h2>Module 1 &mdash; Network Reconnaissance</h2>
    <p>Reconnaissance is the first phase of a penetration test. The goal is to build
       a complete picture of the target environment before attempting any exploitation.</p>

    <h3>Host Discovery</h3>
    <p>Before scanning ports, identify which hosts are alive on the target network.
       Nmap provides several host discovery techniques:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>nmap -sn 10.20.40.0/24</code> &mdash; Ping sweep (no port scan)</li>
      <li><code>nmap -sn --send-ip 10.20.40.0/24</code> &mdash; ICMP echo only</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Port Scanning</h3>
    <p>Once live hosts are identified, enumerate open TCP/UDP ports:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>SYN scan</strong> (<code>-sS</code>): stealthy half-open scan (requires root)</li>
      <li><strong>Connect scan</strong> (<code>-sT</code>): full TCP handshake (no root needed)</li>
      <li><strong>UDP scan</strong> (<code>-sU</code>): slower, but covers UDP services (DNS, SNMP)</li>
      <li><strong>Top ports</strong>: <code>--top-ports 100</code> for quick wins</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="highlight">
      <strong>Key command:</strong> <code>nmap -sV -sC -O -p 22,80,443,3306,8080 10.20.40.10</code><br>
      Combines: version detection (<code>-sV</code>), default scripts (<code>-sC</code>), OS fingerprinting (<code>-O</code>)
    </div>

    <h3>Service and Version Enumeration</h3>
    <p>Knowing which service version is running is critical for vulnerability mapping.
       Outdated versions often have public CVEs. Key flags:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>-sV</code>: probe open ports for service/version info</li>
      <li><code>--version-intensity 5</code>: aggressive version detection (0&ndash;9 scale)</li>
      <li><code>-A</code>: shorthand for <code>-sV -sC -O --traceroute</code></li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Saving Scan Output</h3>
    <p>Always save scan results for your vulnerability report:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>-oN scan.txt</code> &mdash; human-readable</li>
      <li><code>-oX scan.xml</code> &mdash; XML (machine-parseable)</li>
      <li><code>-oA scan</code> &mdash; all formats simultaneously</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Checklist &mdash; Reconnaissance</h3>
    <div class="checklist">
      <label><input type="checkbox"> I have identified all live hosts in the target range</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox"> I have enumerated open ports on the primary target host</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox"> I have identified service names and version numbers for each open port</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox"> I have saved Nmap output in XML format to the results directory</label>
    </div>
    <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="showTab('module2', document.querySelectorAll('nav button')[2])">Next: Module 2 &rarr;</button>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- MODULE 2 TAB -->
<div id="module2" class="tab">
  <div class="card">
    <span class="badge theory">Theory</span>
    <h2>Module 2 &mdash; Vulnerability Scanning and Classification</h2>
    <p>After enumeration, the next step is to identify vulnerabilities in the discovered
       services and classify them by severity and exploitability.</p>

    <h3>Nmap Scripting Engine (NSE)</h3>
    <p>NSE scripts extend Nmap with vulnerability detection capabilities. Key script categories:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>default</strong> (<code>-sC</code>): safe, informational scripts run automatically</li>
      <li><strong>vuln</strong>: checks for known CVEs and misconfigurations</li>
      <li><strong>auth</strong>: tests for default/weak credentials</li>
      <li><strong>http-enum</strong>: web application directory and file enumeration</li>
      <li><strong>ssh-auth-methods</strong>: lists supported SSH authentication methods</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="highlight">
      <strong>Example:</strong> <code>nmap --script=vuln,http-enum,ssh-auth-methods 10.20.40.10</code>
    </div>

    <h3>CVSS Scoring</h3>
    <p>The Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS v3.1) rates severity from 0 to 10:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Critical</strong> (9.0&ndash;10.0): immediate remediation required</li>
      <li><strong>High</strong> (7.0&ndash;8.9): patch within days</li>
      <li><strong>Medium</strong> (4.0&ndash;6.9): scheduled remediation</li>
      <li><strong>Low</strong> (0.1&ndash;3.9): address when feasible</li>
    </ul>
    <p>For each finding, record: CVE ID (if known), CVSS base score, attack vector
       (network/local/adjacent), and whether privileges are required.</p>

    <h3>Common Vulnerability Classes to Look For</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Default credentials</strong>: admin/admin, admin/password, root/root</li>
      <li><strong>Outdated software versions</strong>: cross-reference with NVD or ExploitDB</li>
      <li><strong>Open ports unnecessarily exposed</strong>: databases (3306), admin panels</li>
      <li><strong>Weak SSH configuration</strong>: password auth enabled, root login permitted</li>
      <li><strong>Web application vulnerabilities</strong>: SQLi, XSS, IDOR, path traversal (DVWA)</li>
      <li><strong>Missing TLS/HTTPS</strong>: sensitive data transmitted in cleartext</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Checklist &mdash; Vulnerability Scanning</h3>
    <div class="checklist">
      <label><input type="checkbox"> I have run NSE vuln scripts against all discovered services</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox"> I have identified at least one web application vulnerability (DVWA)</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox"> I have checked SSH for password authentication and weak credentials</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox"> I have assigned a CVSS severity rating to each finding</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox"> I have saved vulnerability scan output to /opt/pentest/results/</label>
    </div>
    <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="showTab('module3', document.querySelectorAll('nav button')[3])">Next: Module 3 &rarr;</button>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- MODULE 3 TAB -->
<div id="module3" class="tab">
  <div class="card">
    <span class="badge theory">Theory</span>
    <h2>Module 3 &mdash; Reporting and Recommendations</h2>

    <h3>Vulnerability Report Structure</h3>
    <p>A professional vulnerability report documents findings clearly so a technical team
       can prioritise and remediate them. Each finding should include:</p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Finding title</strong>: concise, descriptive (e.g., &ldquo;Default Credentials on DVWA Admin Account&rdquo;)</li>
      <li><strong>Affected host/service</strong>: IP, port, service name and version</li>
      <li><strong>Vulnerability description</strong>: what the issue is and why it matters</li>
      <li><strong>CVE / CVSS</strong>: reference ID and base score (if applicable)</li>
      <li><strong>Evidence</strong>: Nmap output excerpt, screenshot, or command output</li>
      <li><strong>Remediation recommendation</strong>: specific, actionable steps</li>
      <li><strong>Priority</strong>: Critical / High / Medium / Low</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Remediation Recommendations</h3>
    <p>Good remediation recommendations are specific and implementable:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Default credentials</strong>: &ldquo;Change DVWA admin password immediately; enforce password complexity policy (min 12 chars, uppercase, digit, special character).&rdquo;</li>
      <li><strong>SSH password auth</strong>: &ldquo;Disable PasswordAuthentication in /etc/ssh/sshd_config; enforce public-key authentication only.&rdquo;</li>
      <li><strong>Outdated service</strong>: &ldquo;Upgrade MariaDB from 10.x to latest stable; subscribe to vendor security advisories.&rdquo;</li>
      <li><strong>Missing TLS</strong>: &ldquo;Enable HTTPS with a valid certificate; configure HTTP-to-HTTPS redirect; set HSTS header.&rdquo;</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Submitting Your Report to Gitea</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Clone your trainee repository: <code>git clone http://report-repo.internal:3000/cyberrange-2b/vuln-report-&lt;your-id&gt;</code></li>
      <li>Create your report file: <code>VULNERABILITY-REPORT.md</code></li>
      <li>Include all findings using the structure above</li>
      <li>Commit and push: <code>git add . && git commit -m "Add vulnerability report" && git push</code></li>
    </ol>
    <div class="warn">
      <strong>Authorisation boundary:</strong> All scanning and exploitation attempts must remain
      within the target range 10.20.40.0/24. Activity outside this range is unauthorised
      and will be flagged.
    </div>

    <h3>Checklist &mdash; Reporting</h3>
    <div class="checklist">
      <label><input type="checkbox"> My report covers at least three distinct findings</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox"> Each finding includes CVE/CVSS where applicable</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox"> Each finding has a specific, actionable remediation recommendation</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox"> I have included Nmap output evidence for each finding</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox"> I have pushed my report to my Gitea repository</label>
    </div>
    <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="showTab('exercise', document.querySelectorAll('nav button')[4])">Start Practical Exercise &rarr;</button>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- EXERCISE TAB -->
<div id="exercise" class="tab">
  <div class="card">
    <span class="badge exercise">Practical Exercise</span>
    <h2>Network Vulnerability Identification Exercise</h2>
    <p>You are now ready to begin the practical exercise against the CYNET-like lab network.</p>

    <h3>Step 1 &mdash; Run the pre-configured scan script</h3>
    <p>From your pentest workstation terminal:</p>
    <div class="url-box">sudo /opt/pentest/scripts/nmap-scan.sh</div>
    <p>This runs host discovery, service enumeration, and vulnerability scripts against the target (10.20.40.0/24).
       Results are saved to <code>/opt/pentest/results/</code>.</p>

    <h3>Step 2 &mdash; Review and extend your findings</h3>
    <p>Open the saved Nmap XML and text reports. For web services, explore
       the DVWA application at:</p>
    <div class="url-box">http://10.20.40.10/</div>
    <p>Default credentials for DVWA: <code>admin / password</code></p>
    <p>Try additional targeted scans as needed:</p>
    <div class="url-box">nmap --script=http-enum,http-title -p 80 10.20.40.10</div>

    <h3>Step 3 &mdash; Compile and submit your vulnerability report</h3>
    <p>Document your findings in Markdown and push to your Gitea repository:</p>
    <div class="url-box">http://report-repo.internal:3000/</div>

    <form id="reportForm" onsubmit="submitReport(event)" style="margin-top:16px;">
      <div style="margin-bottom:12px;">
        <label style="font-size:14px;font-weight:bold;">Your name / trainee ID</label><br>
        <input type="text" id="trainee" required style="width:100%;padding:8px;margin-top:4px;border:1px solid #ccc;border-radius:4px;">
      </div>
      <div style="margin-bottom:12px;">
        <label style="font-size:14px;font-weight:bold;">Gitea report URL (after push) *</label><br>
        <input type="url" id="reportUrl" required style="width:100%;padding:8px;margin-top:4px;border:1px solid #ccc;border-radius:4px;"
               placeholder="http://report-repo.internal:3000/cyberrange-2b/vuln-report-...">
      </div>
      <div style="margin-bottom:12px;">
        <label style="font-size:14px;font-weight:bold;">Vulnerabilities found (one per line, format: Port/Service — Description) *</label><br>
        <textarea id="findings" required rows="6" style="width:100%;padding:8px;margin-top:4px;border:1px solid #ccc;border-radius:4px;font-size:13px;"
                  placeholder="Example:&#10;80/HTTP — DVWA default credentials (admin/password), CVSS 9.8&#10;22/SSH — Password authentication enabled, weak password policy, CVSS 7.5&#10;3306/MySQL — Exposed database port, no external access restriction, CVSS 5.3"></textarea>
      </div>
      <div style="margin-bottom:12px;">
        <label style="font-size:14px;font-weight:bold;">How many critical/high severity findings did you identify?</label><br>
        <input type="number" id="criticalCount" min="0" max="20" style="width:80px;padding:8px;margin-top:4px;border:1px solid #ccc;border-radius:4px;">
      </div>
      <button type="submit" class="btn btn-danger">Submit Exercise Checkin</button>
    </form>
    <div id="reportResult" style="display:none;" class="highlight" style="margin-top:16px;"></div>
  </div>
</div>

</main>

<footer>
  CyberRangeCZ &mdash; PUC2-Sub Case 2b &mdash; Hands-on Educational Platform &mdash;
  Report Repository: <a href="http://report-repo.internal:3000/" style="color:#4a9fd4;">http://report-repo.internal:3000/</a>
  &mdash; Dashboard: <a href="http://reporting.internal:3000/" style="color:#4a9fd4;">http://reporting.internal:3000/</a>
</footer>

<script>
function showTab(id, btn) {
  document.querySelectorAll('.tab').forEach(t => t.classList.remove('active'));
  document.querySelectorAll('nav button').forEach(b => b.classList.remove('active'));
  document.getElementById(id).classList.add('active');
  btn.classList.add('active');
}

function submitReport(e) {
  e.preventDefault();
  var trainee      = document.getElementById('trainee').value;
  var reportUrl    = document.getElementById('reportUrl').value;
  var findings     = document.getElementById('findings').value;
  var criticalCount = document.getElementById('criticalCount').value;

  var result = document.getElementById('reportResult');
  result.style.display = 'block';
  result.innerHTML =
    '<strong>Exercise check-in submitted.</strong><br>' +
    'Trainee: ' + trainee + '<br>' +
    'Report URL: <a href="' + reportUrl + '">' + reportUrl + '</a><br>' +
    'Findings documented: ' + findings.split('\n').filter(function(l){ return l.trim(); }).length + '<br>' +
    'Critical/High findings: ' + (criticalCount || '0') + '<br><br>' +
    'Your instructor will review your Gitea report and provide feedback.<br>' +
    '<a href="http://reporting.internal:3000/">View Cohort Dashboard &rarr;</a>';
}
</script>

</body>
</html>
